uk.co.kring

Class Prim

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.co.kring.Multex
      • uk.co.kring.Symbol

          • uk.co.kring.Prim
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Macro, Majar, ThreadPrim

    public abstract class Prim
extends UnitSymbol
    An abstract class representing a primitive Java operation. Primitives can be loaded from the "plug" sub-package automatically by using the simple class name with a lowercase first letter (like a method name).

      • simple

        protected boolean simple()
        Defines the simple state of not needing threading. Simple is fine for most plugin loading as each load is an instance. For builtin primitives needing instance per use it requires using the thread primitive class instead of this class.
        Returns:
        true if simple. The default is simple.

      • optionReplace

        protected Multex optionReplace()
        Description copied from class: Multex
        Returns an effective clone under executive speed conditions. Some classes return singleton instances. This is to allow multi-threading by supplying a new set of instance variables.
        Overrides:
        optionReplace in class UnitSymbol
        Returns:
        the replacement or this self for no replacement.
